        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/david_bu3ker/{size}/319725_2.png",
        "created_at": "2016-01-03T23:25:50.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p><a href=\"http://www.cellartracker.com/note.asp?iWine=327589&amp;iNote=5433140\"><strong>2005 Domaine Denis Bachelet C\u00f4te de Nuits Villages</strong></a> <em>- France, Burgundy, C\u00f4te de Nuits, C\u00f4te de Nuits Villages (1/3/2016)</em><br>\nJust barely starting to develop at age 10+, the aromatics of this wine show some complexity, though still quite a lot of primary fruit. Every once in a while I catch a whiff of earth, herbs and flowers that tells me the future is going to be beautiful. Maybe another year or 18 months until I try another bottle. I don\u2019t want to go too long, as it\u2019s getting close to really being something.</p>\n<p><em>Posted from <a href=\"http://www.cellartracker.com/\">CellarTracker</a></em><br>\n<img src=\"/uploads/db3686/original/3X/5/4/54cf3a7bacbc81bd5c8f73589427232199ba356a.jpeg\" alt=\"image.jpeg\" data-base62-sha1=\"c6g5Jh5m7FEr8yrIgKycnshpAdI\" width=\"480\" height=\"480\"></p>",
